Covergeist is just a group of friends who like to play music and party with friends.

Justin is the singer and guitar player. He is from Colorado and has quite an interesting story. He was the intern on Taylor Swift's first album, he was a child actor starring in Chrysler commercials and even a Power Rangers Underwear commercial, Justin got fired from Quad Studios for playing Billy Gibbons (ZZTop) guitar, Justin is one of the most distinct and recognizable songwriters and personalities in Nashville, Justin also has a publishing company, record label and invention center, and Justin is also a political activist, poet, painter, potter, pot head and spiritual guru. He is very friendly and personable, yet easily annoyed and explosive and spontaneous, regularly destroying the set at shows. Find him on facebook or at Covergeist's next show and he'd love to talk to ya.

There is an ever-rotating cast of bass players. In the 4 years Covergeist has been a band they have had over 10 bass players. Most likely they are unable to handle Justin's pre-madonna attitude and extreme work-aholic behavior.

David is the drummer of Covergeist. Many people believe he is the next great drummer in Rock N Roll. His sound is like a love child of John Bonham, Keith Moon and Travis Barker. He plays a pink sparkley drum set and rutinely jumps up on his drum thrown screaming and knocks over his kit. He is tall. He could've been a basketball player but he liked to party to much. He is smart, with a degree in computer technology and mathematics. He likes to play rediculous fills and strange time-signatures. He's good looking... there is an instance when a Batchelorette party came to a Covergeist show and actually ripped his underwear off and he finished the set naked. Other than that he is wholesome.
